@startuml 06-peer-to-peer-style
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

skinparam component {
    BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    BorderColor #1565C0
    BorderThickness 2
}

title Peer-to-Peer Architectural Style

component "Peer A" as pa {
    portin "in" as pa_in
    portout "out" as pa_out
}

component "Peer B" as pb {
    portin "in" as pb_in
    portout "out" as pb_out
}

component "Peer C" as pc {
    portin "in" as pc_in
    portout "out" as pc_out
}

component "Peer D" as pd {
    portin "in" as pd_in
    portout "out" as pd_out
}

pa_out <--> pb_in : bidirectional
pa_out <--> pc_in : bidirectional
pb_out <--> pc_in : bidirectional
pb_out <--> pd_in : bidirectional
pc_out <--> pd_in : bidirectional

note top of pa
  All peers are **equal**
  - Can provide services
  - Can consume services
  - No central authority
end note

note bottom of pd
  **Symmetric relationships**
  Any peer can interact
  with any other peer
end note

legend bottom
  |= Characteristic |= Description |
  | Equality | All components have equivalent capabilities |
  | Symmetry | Any peer can initiate or respond |
  | Distribution | No central point of control or failure |
  | Scalability | New peers join without central coordination |
endlegend

@enduml
